Create an instance
gp2 and 8gb
Connect in terminal

yum install httpd -y
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd

Goto EC2
Click on Volume
Click on create Volume
Give Volume type as GP2
Give size=5
Select availability zone as 1a
Create Volume
Give name to the created volume
Select the created volume
Click on Actions
Click on attach Volume
Select the Instance created (identifying by its name)
Give Device name = /dev/sdb
Attach volume


Goto terminal
lsblk
(Under NAME copy the first name... would look something like "xdva1 or xdva'n')
blkid
fdisk -l
mkfs.ext4 /dev/<paste the name copied>
mkdir /data
mount /dev/<paste the name copied> /data
cd /data
touch training.txt{1..10}
ll

ebs attach vol





